description: Delays in being contacted are due to "significant increase in demand", the Government of Jersey say.
title: Jersey delays in Covid-19 testing and contact tracing
title_page: Jersey delays in Covid-19 testing and contact tracing - BBC News
maintext: The government asked people who believed they had been in direct contact of someone with the virus to self-isolate for 48 hours and await the contact tracing team to get in touch.
